The article discusses the House Republican budget for fiscal year 2016 and criticizes it for its focus on tax cuts for the wealthy while cutting investments in the middle class. The article argues that the Republican budget would return to failed top-down economics and harm the economy and working families. It compares the Republican budget to the President's budget, which focuses on strengthening the middle class and making critical investments in areas such as education, research, and infrastructure. The article also highlights specific cuts that the Republican budget would make to programs such as education, job training, and healthcare. It concludes by stating that the Republican budget would limit opportunities for the middle class and jeopardize economic growth.